commit.message:
Fix issue where ffmpeg may occasionally hang (#98)

Debugging revealed that ffmpeg was occasionally throwing
a strange error expecting input of some sort.
https://unix.stackexchange.com/a/36411 reveals that this
is a semi-common issue when running a command in a loop,
and is resolved by setting stdin to /dev/null to ensure
that ffmpeg is not consuming anything to stdin from the loop.

verification.payload:
tree 3bf8b39d1c5fb345103a9ab7fdece82f1bb7c16d
parent 7c974f7396a5c6e459f7c6033674ad7144e820a8
author Josh Holmer <jholmer.in@gmail.com> 1633100989 -0400
committer GitHub <noreply@github.com> 1633100989 +0200

Fix issue where ffmpeg may occasionally hang (#98)

commit.message: undo file rename

updates (#91)

* add a fallback font for Debian-based systems

dejavu fonts are stored in a different location on Debian/Ubuntu

https://packages.debian.org/buster/all/fonts-dejavu-core/filelist

* add {{video_bit_rate}} parameter (fixes #90)

* use BMP instead of PNG for faster captures

this is larger than PNG, but there's no time wasted compressing the temporary file and it's unlikely that the few extra megabytes of disk space matters

Update README.md (#71)

* Remove redundant fallback.
allow use of --ignore-errors without --recursive

Integrated possibility to use a configuration file (#67)

Default path is ${HOME}/.config/vcsi.conf
Defaults on ArgumentParser are adjusted according to the configuration file if it exists
--config or -c can be used to load a specific configuration file
